Jerry L Hollis

WHATDIDWELLWITHAPP__C: Dr. Lane was thorough in her exam--even referring to a wall chart of the ear.  Her subsequent diagnosis was logical and comforting.  She thoroughly explained her proposed treatment.
WHOCONSIDERPRIMARY__C: A primary care doctor outside ofÂ Everside Health
TESTIMONIALTEXT__C: Dr. Lane did help me to see that the discomfort and compromised hearing problem I had after landing in a commercial airplane was most likely a sinus infection that I did not know I had.  I stopped at the clinic on my way into my office building at 7:45 am, described my symptoms to the medical assistant, and asked if I could see the doctor that day.  I was offered an 11:15 appt.  My very good visit started promptly at 11:15.  I walked out of the clinic 30 minutes later with 3 medicines that altogether cost me $12!  I begin taking them immediately, and by mid-Saturday afternoon, I felt like I was nearly 100% again.  (I will, however, continue to take the prescribed medicine as directed.  I saved time, money, and had a very good visit with Dr. Lane.  I must say that EVERY visit I have had with her has been great!
PHYSICIANWELCOMESTATEMENT__C: Welcome to my Paladina Health Practice!

TESTIMONIALTEXT__C: They have helped me in medical crisis in the past, with quick evaluation and diagnosis.  Currently, they are assisting with a chronic condition that has subtle symptoms and many doctors are not willing to dig into the testing required to determine the real status.  My test results have come back from the fuller test panel and shows there is a significant issue - now we can deal with it.  Not great news is actually great news because now I have the full real story and can be hopeful for future changes!

WHATDIDWELLWITHAPP__C: This was my first time meeting Beth; she is amazing! She was friendly and kind, listened intently, understood my concerns, and met my needs.
TESTIMONIALTEXT__C: Last year, when I woke up one morning and couldn't feel my legs, the clinic made a place for me to see Dr. Dave Wester right away. Over the course of the next couple of days, Dave referred me to the spine center and kept up with me daily. When the spine center didn't have time to complete testing, Dave encouraged me to go directly to UW Madison ER, where I was told it was a good thing I had come to them. Dave continued to check on me during my hospital stay and even after I came home. My husband and sons all appreciate his genuine care and think the world of him too.

WHATDIDNOTWELLWITHAPP__C: First was Sandrea!  She was very patient with me during my appointment set up.  I lost a signal while speaking to her, and SHE called me back.  First class! The attention to detail from the staff was great.  Even Lydia --- first nurse yesterday was very pleasant and helped me relax by talking about nail polish.  It was just a good visit!
TESTIMONIALTEXT__C: Melanie, my FNP, saved me $1100!  She offered me a coupon for a new medication that would work like the one I was taking.  She called it in, and I went to pick up at the pharmacy where I paid $25!  I mean, really?  She took the time to compare meds with me and recommend something much cheaper that might even perform better.  I am so excited to work with her and even recommended her to another co-worker after I left the appointment.

Everything!
The office staff is great, Dr Sowinski was very thorough in the labs he ran, if nothing else but just for my peace of mind. I appreciate the time spent, and the fact that the dr himself made the follow up call in case there were any questions. 
This is a great medical facility!
TESTIMONIALTEXT__C:
The office staff is prompt and friendly, and Dr. Sowinski is a gem! Heâ€™s one of those rare doctors that takes enough time for a patient to feel truly heard. I appreciate that he wants to get to root issues rather than just rapid-fire prescription writing. Heâ€™s well-balanced in that he allows for more natural treatments when thatâ€™s what a patient is more comfortable with, but respectfully brings in more modern medicine where the natural treatments fall short. Heâ€™s knowledgeable, but still answers questions thoroughly and in a clear way.  Iâ€™ve never felt rushed during  a conversation with him as is the case with most doctors, and it blows my mind that HE is often the one who actually makes the follow up calls. Iâ€™m a caretaker for my aging parents and we spend a LOT of time in doctors offices, and I can say with certainty that this quality of medical care is very rare. 
Iâ€™m thankful to have stumbled upon him!
PHYSICIANWELCOMESTATEMENT__C: Welcome to my Paladina Health Practice!

WHATDIDWELLWITHAPP__C: I know it isn't a very high bar to hurdle, but Dr. Peterson is the best doctor I've seen in a very long time.  He is thorough, explains things well...perhaps too well sometimes...and looks at the whole picture when it comes to any given issue and doesn't just throw a pill at it.
WHATDIDNOTWELLWITHAPP__C: I wish they would still require, not just encourage, mask use.
TESTIMONIALTEXT__C:
When Everside (formerly Paladina) was introduced, we  were skeptical...figuring it was just a cheap, cost-cutting option for healthcare.  Boy was I wrong.  When we finally tried it after being fed up with current doctors, we found the doctor at the local Everside office to spend much more time with us, trying to understand issues and come up with more appropriate and complete solutions instead of just throwing pills at symptoms.  The doctor we have been seeing seems very knowledgeable and caring.  I have been nothing but impressed and only wished we had switched long before we did.  When was the last time a doctor (not staff, not stuck in the exam room waiting, but the actual doctor) spent more than 10 minutes with you? Ours spends as much time as is needed to get a complete picture of an issue, diagnose, and explain...often in excess of 30 minutes.  Happy to say we now have a good plan for one of my health issues, without the side effects of the treatments from the other doctor. 

This is how healthcare should work...not the "lets push as many patients through as fast as possible" approach others seem to take.  Keep up the good work Everside, show the rest of the US how "the greatest healthcare in the world" is supposed to be for the average American.
PHYSICIANWELCOMESTATEMENT__C: Welcome to my Paladina Health Practice!

WHATDIDWELLWITHAPP__C: I had been ill for 9 days and had a fever. Both Shannon and Lindsey came out to my car for safety concerns. My Covid test came out negative. Lindsey prescribed Prednisone and Antibiotics. They were able to fill my prescriptions right there at the office in just a few minutes.  That was so awesome!! Huge time saver and no copay!!
TESTIMONIALTEXT__C:
I have always had excellent service and care from the staff at Evercare Staff. Dr Karl Trieber is now our family's primary care physician. I can get in for an appointment within a day. How awesome is that. Since they have a starter pharmacy there, it is very convenient to have scripts filled there when possible. All scripts I have needed came with no copay.  Such a time and financial saver. Not having to drive to another pharmacy, wait for 20-30 minutes while my prescriptions are being filled, plus than there is a copay.

I couldn't do blood work that day because I had not fasted, since I didn't know that blood would be drawn.  So my original appointment turned into just driving all the way to the clinic to schedule a blood draw and different day for my physical.  
     I think it would be helpful and save everyone time if the employee scheduling appointments or the app used to schedule appointments made it clear that you need blood work done before meeting with a provider for your physical.

TESTIMONIALTEXT__C: I scheduled my first appointment with Everside expecting that I would likely only go there temporarily until I found a clinic a little closer to my new home. But I am so impressed with the staff and how attentive they are to both big and small medical issues that I am planning to make it the primary place I go for medical care. I have been offered phone appointments and virtual appointments when needed, and my â€œin personâ€ appointments have been extremely thorough and helpful. My health is definitely improved since my first appointment, and my husband and I have both found we are much better about staying on top of medical appointments and our health now that we have a great clinic where we feel confident we will have a good experience and where any medical concerns will be addressed and resolved quickly.
PHYSICIANWELCOMESTATEMENT__C: Welcome to my Paladina Health Practice!

WHATDIDWELLWITHAPP__C: I love Everside Health. I have been going to this clinic for the past years. The front staff are very courteous and quick to support.
TESTIMONIALTEXT__C:
As a family, we have been using Dr. Kristin Everett for the past many years and hands down she is the best PCP we have had, she always goes above and beyond in listening and taking care of us. We are very sad that she is leaving and now I will need to find another Dr within Everside. 
Dr. McBrearty is also amazing with my 7 month old baby. He too goes above and beyond in doing everything right for her, so happy we have the best Dr for our kids within Everside. 

The only downfall is there isn't much locations around Littleton area with good female doctors. I have met Drs at Belmar and DTC location and they are nothing compared to Dr. Everett. Also, there isn't someone available at the front desk to answer phones frequently, will have to call a couple of times till we get to talk to someone. Another concern is, i cannot schedule appointments for my kids via the app from a parent profile.
PROVIDERBIOSHORT__C: Dr. Kristin Everett is a board certified family practice physician who earned her medical degree in 1996 at Temple University School of Medicine in Philadelphia. She completed her residency in 1999 at Abington Memorial Hospital in Pennsylvania.

WHATDIDWELLWITHAPP__C: The staff is ALWAYS so nice! I always feel like I get excellent care!
TESTIMONIALTEXT__C: When my Husband was killed in a motorcycle accident almost 5 years ago, Dr. Mitcheff came to the visitation,  which was so kind, he told me if I needed any medication I'm sure he could tell I was in shock, to call the clinic & they would get me right in. I only took 2 weeks off work, my 3rd day back after getting ready for work, I couldn't leave to go to work. I had hysterical crying, getting on with what was my new life was too much. I called the clinic & they told me Dr. Mitcheff had already told them if I called to tell me to come right in. He gave me a mild antidepressant to take, he explained everything about it, it wasn't habit forming, ect. I took that for 6 months, it kept me on an even keel to be able to function, after 6 months I felt like I was OK to face my new life. If Dr. Mitcheff hadn't came to the visitation & hadn't let me know he would give me something if I needed it, I might not have reached out to him. I believe I would not have gotten through those first 6 month's without that medication & I will always be greatful to him for coming to Tom's visitation & for helping me get through the worst time of my life.
PHYSICIANWELCOMESTATEMENT__C: Welcome to my Paladina Health Practice!
reviews: nan the staff is always so nice  i always feel like i get excellent care  nan
Reviews: The staff is ALWAYS so nice! I always feel like I get excellent care!

WHATDIDWELLWITHAPP__C: You were kind, courteous, and prompt in helping to treat me.
WHATDIDNOTWELLWITHAPP__C: I showed up five minutes late - my bad. However, it seemed like the nurse was stretched a little too thin because it took her at least ten minutes to let the physician know I was there. By the time, the physician met with me, she was under the impression that I was eighteen minutes late, violating your fifteen-minute rule, but I wasn't. Overall, I got what I needed, but it seemed very rushed as my physician basically met with me as they were heading out the door for another appointment.
TESTIMONIALTEXT__C: My doctor was able to help me with an important diagnosis. I was able to avoid a costly visit to an emergency room. I feel better able to treat the condition I'm temporarily dealing with. I was not able to get in with the Provider (from your list) of my choice; therefore, I had to settle for a Nurse Practitioner at another location.  By the way, to rub salt to my wound, there were no other patients at all in that whole building.  It was just me.  So, it's not like they were busy. REASONNPSSCORE__C: I love the service and benefits I receive from Everside clinic but lately it has been extremely frustrating how long it takes to be scheduled for appointments. I thought that the clinic was designed to be able to have quicker access to medical support but that has not been the case for several situations. I had an incident that I knew could be resolved in a quick visit and some medicine they could easily subscribe. But they couldn't get me in for a visit for at least a week. I was in enough agony that was not going to work. I had to go to a statcare clinic and pay for that service on top of the medication that was prescribed. Which I would not have had to pay if I had been able to get into the Everside clinic.n That's why I can't give it a higher score.
WHATDIDWELLWITHAPP__C: I love the physician I see. She is so thorough and good at listening. She is so caring and treats you like you're the only one she has to take care of for the day. It's so reassuring.
IMPROVESATISFACTIONWITHPH__C: Not sure how to remedy the situation but it would be nice to be able to get in quickly when there is an urgent issue that really doesn't need ER. But instead I have sent/recommended to statcare on two occasions because they couldn't get me in in a timely manner. Once when I had a horrible poison ivy reaction and another time when I had a painful UTI.
PHYSICIANWELCOMESTATEMENT__C: Welcome to my Paladina Health Practice!

WHATDIDWELLWITHAPP__C: Upon arrival Jonica Heebink greeted me and was very nice. I was weighed in and brought into a room, had my temp and BP taken both were normal and then Jonica Heebink left to get the Provider. A moment later the Jonica Heebink came in saying Courtney Ballina was requesting a covid test before she would see me?  I said no I didn't want to take a covid test I just wanted my appt. or I was gonna leave. Jonica Heebink asked that she go tell Courtney Ballina that I would not take a covid test. I felt bad that she was put into this situation at all.
WHATDIDNOTWELLWITHAPP__C: Courtney Ballina refused to see me as I would not take a covid test...I came in for a zpack and stated as such on my prior phone call making the appointment, Mind you I had to miss some work hours for this appointment as well. A knock on the door happened, I said yes and it opened and Courtney Ballina stated that since I would not take a covid test she would not assess me and I stated I wanted my money back she said I could get my money back, but I would not be seen by her.   I did not know providers could pick their patients.  Did she not take an oath to care for sick people?  Her personal beliefs have no bearing over my medical health NONE!  I was asking for an antibiotic for my chest cold not her personal opinions and to be refused to be cared for by my medical provider that I PAY INS PREMIUMS FOR, NOT HER and then to be denied IS ABSOLUTELY EGREGIOUS!  She owes me an apology as well as needs to do her job!
WHOCONSIDERPRIMARY__C: A primary care doctor outside ofÂ Everside Health
TESTIMONIALTEXT__C: direct Courtney Ballina that she is supposed to DO HER JOB not dictate her personal agenda beliefs and care for patients who come into the office to be seen by a provider.  She should maybe think about patients' rights and not be so dismissive and rude to people wanting to get an antibiotic to get better.  Maybe if she read my chart or even ask questions, she would see my history and know that I do have asthma and if she really cared she would have given me something so this chest cold does not get worse and cause prolonged issues.
PHYSICIANWELCOMESTATEMENT__C: Welcome to my Paladina Health Practice!

REASONNPSSCORE__C:
I came in for my annual physical.  Normally I would get my physical from my General Practitioner doctor  - but there was a scheduling issue and he could not see me before the Michelin deadline of September 9th.

I went to your office the week before for the blood work required and filled out some paperwork then.  I was also asked in an email online to fill out a questionnaire which I completed - much of the same information as I filled out manually in the office.

I then went to my appointment on the 3rd and checked in where I was told that no information was needed and they would get me soon.  After 15+ minutes of waiting they called me up and asked me to fill out several pages of documents.  These were the same documents that I had filled out the week prior, which I told to the receptionist.  She insisted that I had not filled them out and that I needed to fill them out.  This was very frustrating and she was a little unprofessional.

Five minutes later I was called into the exam room.  I has not finished my paperwork and had to finish during my exam.

When the nurse practitioner came in she apologized to me for having to fill out the forms twice - apparently they found the documents I completed the prior week.

Also, more concerning is that this was not a complete physical.  The PA was very nice, but all she did was take my blood pressure and read through my blood test results with me (which I could have done on my own).  My expectation is for a more thorough examination.  I will keep my appointment with my GP for a more complete and appropriate examination.

Also, it is very frustrating that your system in not connected to the Prisma Healthcare MyChart.  Your predecessor was connected and this made things much easier in keeping our overall medical records up to date.  I would imaging that a large majority of Michelin employees in South Carolina us Prisma as their primary healthcare provider.   Again, there is a certain amount of professionalism that is lacking.  I would strongly recommend you consider making the connection with MyChart like it was done before.

REASONNPSSCORE__C:
Where should I begin:
1. the app is terrible

2. NOTHING...NOTHING transferred from MyChart to Everside. When I called Everside to ask about none of my prescriptions showing up, I was told I could enter them myself. Really?

3. My doctor left the practice (Michelin Family Health Center) soon after the change from MyChart to Everside. Driven off by the ridiculously inept Everside system no doubt.

4. After going through all the steps to make an appointment using the app, at the very end, it just locks up and stalls. I even put my device down and came back 30 minutes later and the circular balls that indicate it is working on the request were still bouncing around. This is not just my experience, but others I have talked to as well.

5. Even given #4, if I call the office to make an appointment, the outgoing message tells me I can make appointments in the app instead. NOPE.

6. My caregivers, (notice I didn't say doctor because there was not a doctor at the office for months until just recently), cannot see any of my records because all my records are in MyChart, which EVERY OTHER MEDICAL PRACTICE I am familiar with uses, except the Michelin Family Health Center. At my last visit, the NP I was seeing was only able to see my history (necessary to give me proper health care) by my logging in to MyChart on my device and showing my health history to the NP. 

7. I see 3 specialists for some conditions I currently have. NONE of them can see any notes from visits to my general care giver at MFHC, because we use this horrible Everside system.

Thank you so very much for sending me this survey. I have wanted to complain since my first experience with Everside, but just didn't really know how to convey my utter and complete dissatisfaction with Everside, and my disappointment in Michelin for saving a buck at the expense of the patients' well-being.
WHATDIDWELLWITHAPP__C: The receptionist was great. The NP who saw me was fantastic. I felt comfortable talking with the NP.
WHATDIDNOTWELLWITHAPP__C:
As far as the people in the office, they are fine people and do as good as they can and I am happy with how I am treated by the people. They just have to work within the constraints of an siloed, terrible system. (That means Everside, by the way. Can't stress that enough). 

For number 6, the next question, I am only selecting "unlikely" because the phrase "Everside Health" exists within that statement. It is not a reflection of the caregiver in any way.
IMPROVESATISFACTIONWITHPH__C: Because every other practice I am aware of uses MyChart...Work like MyChart, link with MyChart, upload history from Mychart, share information back and forth with MyChart, fix the app. Basically, make Everside look like it knows what its doing. Right now it doesn't look that way.
TESTIMONIALTEXT__C: Nothing about my experience with the company Everside Health would prompt a positive review from me.
PHYSICIANWELCOMESTATEMENT__C: Welcome to my Paladina Health Practice!

WHATDIDWELLWITHAPP__C: I have been so impressed with this place... from same day appointment, the beautiful, clean facility, the kindness and professionalism from the staff, the time spent with the dr answering questions and being thorough. I never felt rushed or stupid or like a number. I absolutely love Dr. Alarcon and Ashley. I just can't say enough how much I appreciate them and this location!!
TESTIMONIALTEXT__C: I hadn't been to the doctor in three years as I had just moved to the area, gained employment/insurance and then the pandemic hit. I searched doctors in the area ad nauseam and still didn't know where to go for a primary care doctor. Then I was hit with a bad sinus infection and remembered my employer had sent info about this location opening up. I tried it thinking I probably wouldn't get a same day appointment, but I did. The location, the PA, and the doctor exceeded my expectations. He spent time with me, answered all my questions, and I decided to make him my primary care doctor. I was able to make another appointment very quickly to start on all the things I had put off and to do my annual checkup. Again, he spent time with me, explained everything in detail, actually listened to me, and got everything started for all my needs.  I feel so much better that everything is being addressed. The Doctor and the PA are just amazing! I haven't felt rushed, or stupid for asking questions, or like a number. I really just can't explain how happy I am with my experience here and with Dr. Alarcon. Labs were done in the office at the same visit,  so no need to drive to another location. I even got my lab results back the next day through the portal with explanation from the Doctor. I finally feel like I have a hold on my health again and know where I'll go for any future needs.
PHYSICIANWELCOMESTATEMENT__C: Welcome to my Paladina Health Practice!

WHATDIDWELLWITHAPP__C: My doctor was very thoughtful and helpful listening to my concerns, providing me options and taking the time to help me choose  the best course of treatment. He also took the time to make sure I had other supports in place outside of medication.
TESTIMONIALTEXT__C: After finding out that my previous physician had moved out of state I made an appointment with the first available doctor and I am so happy I did. At the time I was struggling with depression. This doctor was so kind and thoughtful as I explained my situation and previous treatment for this condition. He outlined my options helping me understand the pros and cons so that I was able to make informed choices about my care. After choosing the best option for me we continued to touch base regularly to ensure the treatment plan was effective and made changes when needed. He also provided information on accessing counseling. I have never experienced this level of support and genuine thoughtfulness from a doctor. I cannot say enough wonderful things about this doctor!
